pageContext.claim: “Our border -- our southern border -- is very, very tight. It hasn't been this tight in years. It's being helped by 160 -- more than that -- miles of wall that are going up. I'm trying to get to 450 by the end of the year -- 450 miles. And we'll have 530 miles early next year, and that's really great. It's fully funded. We have all the funds.”
pageContext.analysis: As of the end of May, the Trump administration has built bollard fencing on only three miles of the border that previously had no barrier.
